An early morning inferno yesterday destroyed relief materials worth millions of naira at the Presidential Committee on North-East Initiatives (PCNI)’s warehouse, Baga Road, Maiduguri, Borno State. According to the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN), the fire, which started about 6a.m., destroyed about 400 mattresses, a vehicle and other items in the warehouse. It was learnt that personnel of the Nigeria Security and Civil Defence Corps (NSCDC), police, fire service and residents in the area quickly rushed to the scene of the incident to assist in arresting the fire. The Public Relation’s Officer (PRO), Borno State Fire Service, Mr. Ambursa Pindar, confirmed the incident. He said that a fire truck was deployed to the scene. Pindar said that the fire destroyed some property, including a jeep that was abandoned in the warehouse. Pindar, however, said that no life was lost and nobody sustained injury. He added: “We could not ascertain the cause of the fire because nobody was present at the time of the incident. No security men, nobody was present.” Pindar said that machines and equipment belonging to the Maiduguri Flour Mills, owners of the warehouse, were also not affected. He said that the only part being utilised by PCNI was affected by the fire.T he Head of Media and Communications, PCNI, Mr. Alkasim Abdulkadir, said he was yet to be briefed on the incident by its office in Maiduguri.